review_blob: On tap at Stoutfest during Seattle Beer Week. Everything about it was very impressive. Deep, rich and complex. Hint of tart but no fruit to speak of. Usually the coffee flavor in stouts is pretty basic but it was clear this coffee is different.

If I could drink one for dessert every night, that would almost be enough. I definitely understand it being a little too much for some people. Huge flavor but perfectly balanced. Beautiful tan head. Smells like a cool November day.
beer_name: Fremont Abominable - Bourbon Barrel Coffee Cinnamon

review_blob: From the bottle, this is one of the three best stouts Ive had. Dense head. Beer is black as night. Flavor is nutty/coffee. Good aftertaste, not the best. If you can get it on tap, its absolutely wonderful.
